{\highlight7 <IT>}Avudraham{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*25>}25{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God is not a faroff observer of a mechanism which He created and ignores, but a Living 
Ruler, Who guides the universe and continually maintains it.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*26>}26{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Lit., Your acquisitions: See {\highlight7 <IT>}Genesis{\highlight7 <ITC>} 14:22.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*27>}27{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}I.e., before Creation, See p. 9: God was King before all creatures were created.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*28>}28{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}I.e., after Creation. Ever since Creation, God has been praised and glorified by His 
creatures.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*29>}29{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}See {\highlight7 <IT>}Isaiah{\highlight7 <ITC>} 43:7: “All that is called by My Name, I have created for My glory.”Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Avudraham{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*30>}30{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}“Holy beings” are angels. In Hebrew the word for angels means messenger, and includes 
all the instruments of Divine purpose, whether in human form, or in the forces of 
nature.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Kuzari{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*31>}31{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}A name of God ({\highlight7 <IT>}Genesis{\highlight7 <ITC>} 17:1; 35:11; 43:14 etc.) which refers to His setting boundaries and 
limits throughout creation.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*32>}32{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The Heavenly throne is thus conceived of as surrounded by angels and all the adoring 
heavenly bodies.ÐSee {\highlight7 <IT>}Isaiah{\highlight7 <ITC>} 6:12 {\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*33>}33{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Those of His creatures capable of praising Him do so. The rest are evidence of His 
astonishing wisdom and arouse the others to praise Him.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*34>}34{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Some render {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'f6\'e5\'cc\'f8\'c5\'f0\'e5\'cc{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch  “our Rock.” The Gaon of Vilna, however, maintains that it refers to God 
as our Creator, thus describing Him in the triepochal aspect of His Unity: past, present, and 
future. He {\highlight7 <IT>}was{\highlight7 <ITC>} our Creator, He {\highlight7 <IT>}is{\highlight7 <ITC>} our King, and He {\highlight7 <IT>}will{\highlight7 <ITC>} be our Redeemer.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*35>}35{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}These are the Jewish People, who are sanctified in body and soul. The word Creator implies 
a creation of real substanceÐthe Jewish People rather than angels.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Gaon of Vilna{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*36>}36{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Beloved{\highlight7 <ITC>}Ðthere is no envy, jealousy or rivalry among them. {\highlight7 <IT>}Pure{\highlight7 <ITC>}Ðthey have no selfish or 
ulterior motives; they serve God with all their being.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siddur HaGra{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*37>}37{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Despite the attributes we use to describe Him, He remains holyÐbeyond our conception.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*38>}38{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The yoke of Divine Sovereignty is borne willingly and joyfully by each creature as an 
emblem of his free service to God.{\highlight7 <IT>}ÐS.R. Hirsch{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*39>}39{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}They take care not to precede one another in their praise of God. On the contrary, each 
says to the other, “You begin, because you are greater and more worthy than I.”Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Avos of R’ Nosson{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*40>}40{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The clear speech of the angels is the holy tongue (pure Hebrew).Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Yaavetz{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*41>}41{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Isaiah{\highlight7 <ITC>} 6:3. {\highlight7 <IT>}Targum Yonoson{\highlight7 <ITC>} paraphrases this verse: “Holy [is God] in the highest heights of 
