{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*77>}77{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The heart and the eyes of a person are the agents of sinÐthe eye sees, the heart desires, and 
thus the person sins.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Tanchuma{\highlight7 <ITC>} cited by {\highlight7 <IT>}Rashi.{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*78>}78{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <IT>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Numbers{\highlight7 <ITC>} 15:37±41.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*79>}79{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The Jew declares his commitment to God, and states that His precepts are not forced upon 
him. On the contrary, they are beloved, cherished, delightful and pleasant to him.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach 
Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*80>}80{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The teachings of Torah are correct in their totality. They lack nothing and are eternally 
valid for all situations.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*81>}81{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Even those precepts that are not easily understood and appear to contradict human 
nature, are accepted by us.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*82>}82{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}All that was affirmed above in Shema.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*83>}83{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}After having affirmed that all that was said in {\highlight7 <IT>}Shema{\highlight7 <ITC>} is true, firm, certain, enduring, etc., 
we take an oath and testify that we accept the “yoke of heaven” upon ourselves as did our fathers 
before us and as will our children after us, forever and ever. Thus we say in the following prayer: 
“For our fathers, for us, for our children and for our descendantsÐYour word is good and 
lastingÐa Law that will never be abrogated.”Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Kuzari{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*84>}84{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The word {\highlight7 <IT>}help{\highlight7 <ITC>} indicates that the recipient also participated in his rescue, whereas the 
words {\highlight7 <IT>}shield{\highlight7 <ITC>} and {\highlight7 <IT>}deliverer{\highlight7 <ITC>} indicate that the rescue was made without any help from the rescued 
party. Our fathers who were righteous, participated in their rescue, and God “helped” them. 
Since we are not that righteous, God shields and delivers us even though we have no 
merit.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*85>}85{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Alternatively: “Affect mankind to the end of earthly time.” Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Avudraham{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*86>}86{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}“Your Torah” means the basic concepts of the Torah itself, and “Your word” refers to 
ethical concepts, derived from events described in the Torah and by the Prophets.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Siach 
Yitzchok{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*87>}87{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}We refer to God as First and Last only in order to preclude the notion that anything 
existed before Him, and to repudiate the idea that there is an end to His existence. We {\highlight7 <IT>}do not{\highlight7 <ITC>} 
assert that He has a beginning or a fixed term.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Kuzari{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*88>}88{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}See {\highlight7 <IT>}Exodus{\highlight7 <ITC>} 4:22.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*89>}89{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God humbled the Egyptians who were haughty and raised high the Jews who had been 
lowly captives in Egypt.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*90>}90{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}God also helps those who are spiritually impoverished.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Rabbi Yehuda ben Yakar{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*91>}91{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Intrinsically.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*92>}92{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}By others.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*93>}93{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}As it is said, “And a redeemer will come to Zion and to those of Jacob who repent of their 
transgression, said Adonoy” ({\highlight7 <IT>}Isaiah{\highlight7 <ITC>} 59:20).{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*94>}94{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}While God is always referred to as the Redeemer of Israel, this blessing utilizes the past 
